This database is designed as a regions polygon database and is updated when sufficient number of changes have occured to warrant an update. Updates are determined by the needs of the local office. Separate databases are used for maintenance purposes. Boundaries are continually being updated as changes are identified by the Water Districts. The boundaries are not current for all Water </abstract>       <purpose>The Private Water District boundaries database is cooperatively shared between the U.S. Bureau of Reclamation (USBR), Mid-Pacific regional office (MP), MPGIS Service Center and the California Department of Water Resources (DWR). The USBR maintains this database with the voluntary assistance of the Private Water Districts. This database allows the USBR and DWR to display and analyze this information.This database is not intended to be used as a land survey or representation of land for conveyance or tax purposes. The database is available to all users that may require this information.</purpose>     </descript>     <status>       <progress>Unknown</progress>       <update>Unknown</update>     </status>
